posts.name: Luana Picelli
posts.cooked: Hello community, I’m from a FRC team and I just got here to show you something my team has made a while ago. It is a wheel made of PLA covered by an inner tube that we use to give traction to the note. We used this wheel in the 2024 regional and had an impressive result.The cost of the wheel is very low, we spend 1% of what we would spend if we bought from a company, we spend approximately 4 reais ($0.78) excluding labor and electricity. Despite all this, these wheels also had a positive influence on us winning the sustainability award in our rook[ie year, as these wheels were spread over most of the robot. Here’s a video explaining how we made this:

This is sick. Def will look into this.

You guys should look into tube rollers. It’s pretty much has the same purpose but you can elongate it so you don’t have to print so many wheels.

posts.name: Joonoh Lee
posts.cooked:
Yeah heres a thread with better instructions. https://www.chiefdelphi.com/t/how-do-you-make-surgical-tubing-roller/152745/18

We use polycarbonate rollers and float on the Silicone Tubing from WCP using a shopvac. For the ends we just print out some plugs with a hexshape in it. Here’s the Onshape Generator Link.

The cool thing with these is that you can directly put things like pulleys on the endcaps.
